modules.description: This module models a damped spring system using a stateful snapshot that tracks position and velocity. It provides functions to create a spring with specific angular frequency and damping ratio, and to update the spring's state toward a target position over a given time step. Concrete use cases include simulating smooth animations, physics-based UI interactions, and game mechanics involving spring dynamics.

Models a damped spring system with stateful tracking of position and velocity. Exposes functions to initialize a spring with angular frequency and damping ratio, and to advance its state toward a target over a time step. Used for smooth animations, physics-based UIs, and game mechanics requiring spring dynamics.
